text: Not sure if that has much synergy with Chainer, since it just riffs on his ability
I've been really down on wheel effects lately

I've seen them do work, but way more often I've seen them lose games. Some of that is the person casting them, but I think the situations where even the best ones (Wheel of Fortune) are good are vastly outnumbered by the situations they aren't, and I that's rarely a good thing for a card.

I even made a comment the other day on twitter in that regard, and all the defenses I got for them were "They're great if I drop a T1 Sol Ring and Crypt!" or "They work well if I have card W and X and Y and Z in play!" That's a lot of rarely achieved variables you need to line up to have a card be good.
They're consistently great with card draw limiting effects like Narset out and that's about it, if you're looking for consistency.
That said, they're still something I enjoy casting; I find them fun. But you're right that their effect on the game is wildly variable.
they do help with land drops
